    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"stepping away for a moment\" doesn't work. it's not like i can just take a weekend off or go on a vacation and have the feeling go away. the pressure is constant. it's in my head, it's my identity, it's everything. the only way i can actually imagine finding that kind of silence and peace—where nothing can hurt me or demand anything from me ever again—is if it's permanent. it feels like the only way to truly stop the crushing is to just... stop being. does that even make sense?",
